# 10. ３人でセッション！？

Saki: Ichiii! The weather's so perfect today, huh!
Ichika: I see you're in a really good mood. Did something good happen?
Saki: Heh heh heh! Not yet, but I'm going shopping after school. Wanna come with?
Ichika: Ah, so that's what you're after.
Saki: Yup! We've got a band now, so I want to have a keyboard I chose myself.
Saki: I'm prepared to spend all the pocket money I've been saving!
Ichika: Wow, you really are determined. But you know, expensive doesn't necessarily mean best. Why don't you ask the store staff for advice?
Saki: I guess I could do that. Do you see any staff around?
Saki: Oh! It's Shiho!
Shiho: Saki? And Ichika?
Ichika: Shiho...
Saki: Hey, how are you? Haven't seen you since that time in SEKAI!
Saki: What are you up to? Shopping?
Shiho: Yeah. You?
Saki: Hehe! I'm also looking to buy something♪ A synthesizer!
Shiho: Why?
Saki: Because we started a band! Miku and her friend from SEKAI are helping us practice!
Shiho: Are you kidding me? You're doing band practice with Miku?
Shiho: You can just hang out in that weird world and it doesn't bother you?
Saki: It's not weird, it's wonderful!
Saki: So, you're still playing bass, right? Are you in a band?
Shiho: I see where this is going. Listen, I've got no intention of joining your band.
Saki: Oh, don't be like that! I haven't even asked yet!
Shiho: ..... I'm not in a band, but I sometimes play bass at the live house where I work if the usual bassist can't make it.
Shiho: I'm fine on my own.
Ichika: Shiho...
Saki: But...I want to spend more time with you! Lots more! And I want you in our band!
Saki: I want Hona to join too! Let's play together, the four of us!
Shiho: *Sigh*...
Shiho: You haven't changed a bit since elementary school.
Saki: Really? How so?
Shiho: Back then you used to pester me to play with you every day. Even though I kept telling you I wanted to be left alone to play games at home.
Saki: You're making it sound like I was really pushy...
Shiho: You were, and you still are. Just like my sister. In the end, I had no choice but to give in.
Saki: Sorry... But you know, I just really wanted to play with you!
Shiho: .....
Shiho: I joined a band once, in junior high. An older member from the school pop music club invited me.
Shiho: It turned out the other members treated it more like a social club. They couldn't even play a single song half-decently. We got into an argument...
Shiho: And in the end, they kicked me out.
Saki: Shiho...
Shiho: I'm not going to join a band that doesn't take itself seriously.
Ichika: Shiho...
Shiho: Can you learn to play this song by next week?
Saki: What's this? Oh, it's sheet music?
Shiho: If you can play this with me, I'll consider joining your band.
Saki: !!
Saki: I'll learn it! I'll start practicing right away! You too, right, Ichi?
Ichika: Y-Yeah!
Shiho: Okay, I've got to go to work now.
Saki: Woohoo! Ichi, we're going to learn to play this song perfectly! We can do this!
Ichika: Yeah... Saki, thanks. Without you, I'd have given up on Shiho.
Saki: Hehe! I guess it takes someone as stubborn as me!
Saki: We can't waste this chance. We've got to start practicing and master this song!
Saki: But first, I'm buying a new keyboard!
Ichika: Right. Excuse me, could you help us with something?
Shiho: They want me to play with them...
Shiho: I thought it was best if I just kept my distance...
Shiho: Huh? Was that a shooting star?
Little Saki: What was that? A shooting star? Oh no, I missed it! Where did it go?
Little Honami: Saki, shooting stars disappear really quickly. You have to watch the sky carefully to see one.
Little Saki: I'm trying but I can't see any!
Little Ichika: You have to be patient. Let's keep looking.
Shiho: .....
Shiho: Oh... It was just a plane.
Shiho: I guess there's no way you could see a shooting star from here.
